<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-05-06T08:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-05-06T08:25:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6461 Tsana Dam/268:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia (<persName type="from">Southard</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-06T16:00:00+02:35">May 6,
                                        1931—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 7—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Referring to my cable of April 27, 4 p.m., British Chargé
                                d’Affaires has had a reply from London informing him that the Sudan
                                Government considers it premature to press at this time for a
                                conference. Chargé d’Affaires does not intend to say anything to the
                                Ethiopians unless further instructed. In connection with this delay
                                please see my despatch No. 657 of March 7th<note n="16" xml:id="d646fn16">Not printed.</note> and related
                                despatches.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>